<span id="freeTextContainer8598285654375937421">A really great read, there where three stories going on at the same time. My biggest complaint was on my ebook version, you couldn&apos;t tell when it had switched characters. Half the flash backs where filled with quite lovely jokes (primarchs making fun of one another, best one was to Fulgrim. &quot;I hear you do things to your sons...&quot; Yup, I know what that was implying..and I laughed more then I should.) <br/><br/>Dorn and Malcador make cameo appearances, and Malcador delivered my all time favorite line. &quot;You b</span>
  <span id="freeText8598285654375937421" style="display:none">A really great read, there where three stories going on at the same time. My biggest complaint was on my ebook version, you couldn't tell when it had switched characters. Half the flash backs where filled with quite lovely jokes (primarchs making fun of one another, best one was to Fulgrim. "I hear you do things to your sons..." Yup, I know what that was implying..and I laughed more then I should.) <br /><br />Dorn and Malcador make cameo appearances, and Malcador delivered my all time favorite line. "You brothers-such a nest of rivalries. I warned him to make you sisters, that it would make things more civilized. He thought I was joking, I wasn't."<br /><br />I am deliberating on what Fulgrim and Angron would be like...it is a very scary idea. Anyway, great book you should all read it. Defiantly the best by Chris Wright that I have ever read.<br /></span>
