<div id="review_2563898273" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2563898273" />
    <a title="Dave" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18933750-dave"><img alt="Dave" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2563898273?book_show_action=true">Oct 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dave" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dave" href="/user/show/18933750-dave">Dave</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2563898273" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9430171481452803588">I was inclined to give this 5 stars as it so vastly superior to most of the HH dross we are offered but I stuck with a fairer 4.<br/><br/>This book is everything the general series is not. Fun, action packed, tight narrative, good prose (though I will grant the Abnett books tick this particular box as well) and above all just an engaging read. <br/><br/>It helped I was stuck on 3 hours of flights with a 3 hour stop off but I read almost the whole book in a day. It just keeps you reading.<br/><br/>The only criticism is whilst</span>
  <span id="freeText9430171481452803588" style="display:none">I was inclined to give this 5 stars as it so vastly superior to most of the HH dross we are offered but I stuck with a fairer 4.<br /><br />This book is everything the general series is not. Fun, action packed, tight narrative, good prose (though I will grant the Abnett books tick this particular box as well) and above all just an engaging read. <br /><br />It helped I was stuck on 3 hours of flights with a 3 hour stop off but I read almost the whole book in a day. It just keeps you reading.<br /><br />The only criticism is whilst it paints a very interesting and engaging picture of the white scars as a legion (and a nice look at the wolves) it doesn't really build much into the specific characters. They are there to tell the story as opposed to having a tale of their own and none will go down as memorable.<br /><br />The above being said, still a great read and for once a good addition to the series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9430171481452803588" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


