<div id="review_2310196244" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2310196244" />
    <a title="Miles Drake" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/77108412-miles-drake"><img alt="Miles Drake" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1517258599p2/77108412.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2310196244?book_show_action=true">Feb 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Miles Drake" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Miles Drake" href="/user/show/77108412-miles-drake">Miles Drake</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2310196244" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8808060513897186099">While I like the White Scars, and I&apos;m glad to have read a book on their narrative, the choices they made, I felt that it could have used a little more flavor. None of the characters were as memorable as they could have been, and I felt the action scenes were a little more lackluster than they should have been, given whom they are about. <br/>Still, it was by no means a bad read, and it tells an integral part of the story of the Heresy.</span>
  <span id="freeText8808060513897186099" style="display:none">While I like the White Scars, and I'm glad to have read a book on their narrative, the choices they made, I felt that it could have used a little more flavor. None of the characters were as memorable as they could have been, and I felt the action scenes were a little more lackluster than they should have been, given whom they are about. <br />Still, it was by no means a bad read, and it tells an integral part of the story of the Heresy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8808060513897186099" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


