<div id="review_2998682481" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2998682481" />
    <a title="Poovy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17187418-poovy"><img alt="Poovy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1422205016p2/17187418.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2998682481?book_show_action=true">Dec 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Poovy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Poovy" href="/user/show/17187418-poovy">Poovy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2998682481" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15982146468693284034">The white scars are pretty much the forgotten legion in the context of the Horus Heresy and are only briefly mentioned in the other novels/short stories. So it was nice to finally read this book and get a better understanding of Jagatai Khan, the scars and their allegiances.<br/>A lof of gaps are filled in, describing why the White Scars have been so absent from the civil war and also a nice catchup on the space wolves and their regrets over what they did in Prospero.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


