<span id="freeTextContainer12879848937096196022">An excellent antidote to the mediocre &apos;Vulkan Lives&apos;, &apos;Scars&apos; by Chris Wraight has all the character and solid story structure that was missing from that predecessor in this gargantuan series of novels about little plastic men. I&apos;m very much forward to listening to the next one!</span>
  <span id="freeText12879848937096196022" style="display:none">An excellent antidote to the mediocre 'Vulkan Lives', 'Scars' by Chris Wraight has all the character and solid story structure that was missing from that predecessor in this gargantuan series of novels about little plastic men. I'm very much forward to listening to the next one!</span>
